%20Yet%20Hochul%20and%20Adams%20have%20remained%20close%20allies%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20she%20would%20choose%20to%20oust%20him%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgothamist.com%2Fnews%2Fwhat-happens-if-mayor-adams-resigns-or-refuses-to-leave-city-hall%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGothamist%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20New%20York%20City-based%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20second%20scenario%20outlined%20in%20the%20charter%2C%20the%20city%20could%20convene%20a%20never-before-used%20%26quot%3Binability%20committee.%26quot%3B%20The%20committee%20includes%20five%20members%3A%20New%20York%20City's%20top%20attorney%2C%20the%20comptroller%2C%20the%20City%20Council%20speaker%2C%20the%20borough%20president%20serving%20the%20longest%20consecutive%20term%2C%20and%20a%20deputy%20mayor%20that%20the%20mayor%20selects%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fhtml%2Frecords%2Fpdf%2Fsection%25201133_citycharter.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecity%20charter%3C%2Fa%3E%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%2C%20three%20of%20those%20positions%20are%20held%20by%20known%20individuals.%20Adrienne%20Adams%20is%20the%20City%20Council%20Speaker%2C%20Donovan%20Richards%20is%20the%20longest-serving%20borough%20president%2C%20and%20Brad%20Lander%20is%20the%20comptroller%20(and%20running%20for%20mayor%20himself%20in%202025).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERichards%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Lander%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20position%20of%20top%20attorney%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0formally%20known%20as%20corporation%20counsel%20%E2%80%94%20is%20vacant%2C%20though%20Muriel%20Goode-Trufant%20is%20serving%20the%20role%20in%20an%20acting%20capacity.%20Goode-Trufant%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERandy%20Mastro%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20who%20was%20nominated%20by%20Adams%20for%20the%20top%20attorney%20position%2C%20withdrew%20his%20bid%20for%20the%20role%20in%20September%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F09%2F10%2Fnyregion%2Frandy-mastro-eric-adams-lawyer-withdraws.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20unclear%20whom%20Adams%20would%20select%20as%20deputy%20mayor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20out%20of%20five%20committee%20members%20would%20need%20to%20vote%20to%20kick%20Adams%20out%20of%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mayor%20made%20clear%20today%20that%20he%20plans%20to%20continue%20delivering%20for%208.3%20million%20New%20Yorkers%20as%20mayor%2C%26quot%3B%20Fabien%20Levy%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Adams%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa4f32e7-b557-4f56-8931-4e204cbe7bc9%5C%22%3EWho%20would%20replace%20Adams%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-mayor-eric-adams-charges-indicted-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAdams%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20removed%20from%20office%20or%20resigns%2C%20Jumaane%20Williams%2C%20the%20city's%20public%20advocate%2C%20would%20serve%20as%20acting%20mayor.%20Should%20Williams%20not%20be%20able%20to%20serve%2C%20Lander%2C%20the%20comptroller%2C%20would%20take%20over%20until%20a%20special%20election%20is%20held%20for%20mayor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20three%20days%20of%20Adams%20vacating%20Gracie%20Mansion%2C%20Williams%20would%20need%20to%20name%20a%20date%20for%20a%20special%20election.%20According%20to%20city%20rules%2C%20that%20date%20would%20be%20the%20first%20Tuesday%20that's%2080%20days%20after%20Adams%20steps%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20election%20wouldn't%20include%20a%20primary%2C%20so%20candidates%20would%20run%20without%20a%20party%20affiliation.%20Voters%20would%20use%20ranked-choice%20voting%2C%20as%20they%20did%20in%20the%20last%20mayoral%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20howe